data.name: biomaj-daemon

evidence: "Microservice to manage biomaj, acts as a frontend to receive biomaj-cli commands and execute operations" (describes it as a service/frontend application around another tool).
PyPI badge in README: "[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/biomaj-daemon.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/biomaj-daemon)" (indicates distribution via PyPI).

Run instructions show it as a deployed service: "Microservice to manage biomaj...", with commands like `python bin/biomaj_daemon_consumer.py` and `gunicorn ... biomaj_daemon.daemon.biomaj_daemon_web:app`, indicating it supports/controls another research tool rather than performing analyses itself.
